                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and regular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (luminous vivid scarlet, strong scarlet)</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰላ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#14r">14r</locus>, 16r, 20r)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ኢየሱ፡</abbr> for <expan>ኢየሱስ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#15r">15r</locus>, 19v, 22r)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሚካኤ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሚካኤል፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#53v">53v</locus>, 54r, 55r)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰ፡ ለ፡ / ሰ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰአል፡ ለነ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#55r">55r</locus>, 56r)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; two lines on the incipit page of Texts
                           I and II; two lines on the incipit page of Texts II and III, alternating
                           with black lines; initial words of each strophe; elements of quire marks;
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; the
                           word ʾǝnzä (fol. 52r).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A recent supplication formula in marker mentions the name of Gäbrä Giyorgis: <locus target="#8v">fol.  8v</locus>. - Correction written interlineally: <locus target="#39v">fol.  39v</locus>. - Minor notes and scribbles: fols. 1r, 3v, 5r, 12r, 25r, 29v, 30r, 48r, 58v, 60r-v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
